snippet: Tiger Woods, the defending champion, posted a 36-hole total of one-over 145, assuring that he will extend to 14 his streak of consecutive cuts made at the Memorial Tournament.
abstract: Defending champion Tiger Woods makes cut for Memorial Tournament for record 14th consecutive time, despite lackluster play.
lead_paragraph: Tiger Woods, the defending champion, posted a 36-hole total of one-over 145, assuring that he will extend to 14 his streak of consecutive cuts made at the Memorial Tournament.

headline.seo: When Not Sharp, Tiger Woods Knows How to Avoid the Cut
headline.main: Woods Is Not in Top Form at the Memorial, but as Usual, He Makes the Cut
headline.print_headline: Woods Is Not in Top Form at the Memorial, but as Usual, He Makes the Cut
